The '''cryptic honeyeater''' ('''''Meliphaga imitatrix'''''), also known as the '''imitatress honeyeater''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]]. It is found in northeastern [[Queensland]] in [[Australia]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical [[mangrove forest]].<ref name="iucn status 18 November 2021" />

